President Biden has declared a major disaster in Vermont due to severe storms and flooding that occurred in July. Federal funding will be provided to affected individuals and counties for temporary housing, home repairs, and low-cost loans. State and local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, can also receive federal funding for emergency protective measures. Hazard mitigation measures will be implemented statewide. William F. Roy of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations. Damage assessments are ongoing, and more counties and assistance may be designated in the future. Residents and business owners can apply for assistance through various channels. For more information, contact the FEMA news desk.